/**
 * @mainpage AR4 ROBOT Documentation
 * 
 * @section intro_sec Introduction
 * 
 * Complete documentation for the AR4 Robot Control System. This workspace contains
 * all packages for robot control, communication, and utilities.
 * 
 * @section modules_sec Modules
 * 
 * @subsection command_sec Command & Control
 * 
 * High-level robot control and motion planning packages:
 * 
 * - @ref ar_bt_page "Behavior Tree Integration" - BehaviorTree.CPP integration for task sequencing
 * - @ref ar_control_page "Robot Control" - Core robot control, hardware interface, and drive control
 * - @ref ar_motion_planner_page "Motion Planner" - Motion planning functionality
 * - @ref ar_planning_interface_page "Planning Interface" - MoveIt planning interface wrapper
 * - @ref ar_projects_page "Project Manager" - YAML-based motion sequence generator
 * - @ref ar_scene_page "Scene Manager" - 3D scene and mesh management
 * - @ref ar_ui_page "User Interface" - Qt-based UI panels and windows
 * 
 * @subsection communication_sec Communication
 * 
 * Low-level communication and EtherCAT packages:
 * 
 * - @ref ar_comm_page "Communication Library" - ROS2 communication utilities
 * - @ref ar_serial_page "Serial Communication" - Serial port communication
 * - @ref devices_page "Device Management" - Device client/server
 * - @ref master_page "EtherCAT Master" - EtherCAT master and IGH integration
 * 
 * @subsection utilities_sec Utilities
 * 
 * Common utilities and helper libraries:
 * 
 * - @ref ar_common_page "Common Definitions" - Common data structures and definitions
 * - @ref ar_computation_page "Computation" - Mathematical computations and conversions
 * - @ref ar_utils_page "Utilities" - Logging, serialization, and helper functions
 * 
 * @section getting_started Getting Started
 * 
 * For quick start guides, see the README files in individual packages:
 * - @ref ar_bt_page
 * - @ref ar_projects_page
 * - @ref ar_ui_page
 * 
 * @section architecture Architecture Overview
 * 
 * The system is organized in layers:
 * 
 * 1. **Hardware Layer**: EtherCAT communication (master package)
 * 2. **Control Layer**: Drive control and hardware interface (ar_control)
 * 3. **Planning Layer**: Motion planning and execution (ar_motion_planner, ar_planning_interface)
 * 4. **Task Layer**: Behavior trees and project management (ar_bt, ar_projects)
 * 5. **UI Layer**: User interfaces (ar_ui)
 * 
 * @author AR Development Team
 * @date 2026
 */

